                            <comment id="376851" author="adilger" created="Thu, 29 Jun 2023 03:05:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like a large &lt;tt&gt;PAGE_SIZE&lt;/tt&gt; issue and could likely be fixed with a test script change.  As a starting point, the error cases should print &quot;&lt;tt&gt;$LCTL get_param -n osc.&amp;#42;.rpc_stats&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to see if there is anything interesting in the stats when the test fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, when fixing this issue, &lt;tt&gt;test_101g_brw_size_test()&lt;/tt&gt; incorrectly prints &quot;&lt;tt&gt;dd write ${mb} MB blocks failed&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for the &lt;b&gt;read&lt;/b&gt; part of the test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
